  "text": "In the study by Lesage et al. [CITATION_1] , the NOD2 SNP rs72796353 was only found in CD patients, suggesting a potential role in CD development [CITATION_2] . Apart from that, data on this SNP located in the intervening sequence of exon 4 are very limited [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] and there are no data analysing the phenotypic consequences of this SNP in IBD patients. Therefore, we aimed to analyse the association of the NOD2 SNP rs72796353 regarding diseases susceptibility and disease phenotype in a large, well-characterized German IBD cohort (n = 2256).",
